greIfTable.name: greIfTable
greIfTable.description: This Table contains configuration information for GRE interfaces. Each time a new entry is created here, a corresponding entry is created in the ifTable and biboAdmDeviceTable.

greIfEntry.name: greIfEntry
greIfEntry.description: Entries in this table are created by defining a new value for the field greDstIpAddr. Entries may be deleted by setting the field greUseKey to 'delete'.

greIfIndex.name: greIfIndex
greIfIndex.description: The index of the virtual interface. This object identifies a row in the ifTable.

greIfDescr.name: greIfDescr
greIfDescr.description: The name of the virtual interface. The same name will be assigned to the corresponding ifDescr in the ifTable.

greIfMtu.name: greIfMtu
greIfMtu.description: Determines size of the largest datagram which can be sent on the interface, specified in octets (see ifMtu).

greDstIpAddr.name: greDstIpAddr
greDstIpAddr.description: The IP address of the GRE remote partner.

greKey.name: greKey
greKey.description: The optional 32-bit key for this GRE tunnel. Multiple tunnels can be used simultaneously between the two same GRE partners provided each tunnel uses a different key.

greUseKey.name: greUseKey
greUseKey.description: This object indicates, whether the key value specified in greKey should be processed in GRE headers.

greSrcIpAddr.name: greSrcIpAddr
greSrcIpAddr.description: The source IP address used when sending GRE packets. If this value is set to 0.0.0.0, the IP address of the interface used to route packets towards the remote partner will be automatically selected for this purpose.
